headline: The Score: Norfolk Southern, Citigroup, Nvidia and More Stocks That Defined the Week
summary: The U.S. may be getting closer to a transcontinental railroad.  Railroad operator  Union Pacific  is holding talks to acquire its smaller rival  Norfolk Southern  The Wall Street Journal reported Thursday.  In the U.S., no railroad operator currently has a network running coast-to-coast.
